==English==

===Etymology===
From {{ON.}} ''[[kynda]]''

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈkɪndl/}}, {{SAMPA|/"kIndl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-kindle.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪndəl|-ɪndəl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} A [[collective]] term for a group of [[kitten]]s.
#: ''A '''kindle''' of kittens.''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|kindl|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To start (a [[fire]]) or light (a [[torch]]).
#: ''Please '''kindle''' a fire in the [[barbecue]].''
# {{transitive}} To arouse or inspire (a passion, etc).
#: ''He '''kindled''' an enthusiasm for the project in his fellow workers.''

